## Part 6: Putting It All Together — Why This Project Matters

The reason this project is interesting isn't the AI — it's that **the underlying problem is exactly the kind of work agentic AI was invented for**:

- Structured decisions with documented rules
- Heavy lookups across multiple data sources
- Client-specific routing across many similar-but-different policies
- A real but bounded judgment component (Scenario 4)
- High volume, high cost of human labor, low margin for error
- Clear human-in-the-loop fallback

If BNP gets this right, the same pattern transfers naturally to FX rates (#80), dividend control (#85), data quality checks (#78), Colibri static data (#77), and even the asset creation workflow (#84). The pricing exception use case is the wedge — succeed there and the agentic operating model scales horizontally across DA operations.

The risks are real (capacity, key-person dependency, regulatory explainability, vendor API stability) but the use case itself is well-chosen.

